23/09/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Mayors of 12 Bulgarian, six Macedonian and nine Serbian border municipalities meet on Friday (23 September) in the Bulgarian town of Kocherinovo. The focus will be co-operation possibilities, particularly the establishment of common economic, commercial and cultural goals to help them benefit fully from EU pre-accession programmes. The mayors will also debate strategy for the establishment of a Morava-Pchinya-Struma Euro region. (News.bg - 23/09/05) 
